================
File Permissions
================

1) Absoulte Mode 

2) Symbolic Mode 

u --> user (owner)
g --> group 
o --> others 

r --> read
w --> write 
x --> execute

 u   g   o
rwx rwx rwx 

--------------
777 permission
--------------
  u     g     o
r w x r w x r w x
4 2 1 4 2 1 4 2 1 
  7     7     7    


**********
Use-Cases:
**********

i) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to file by using absolute mode?

ii) How do I grant the user (owner) read and write, the group read-only, and all others read-only to file? 

iii) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode?

iv) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode and this permissions must be associated to all files and directories/sub-directories underneath this directory?

****************
1) Absolute Mode
****************

i) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to file by using absolute mode?

A) chmod 740 file_name

ii) How do I grant the user (owner) read and write, the group read-only, and all others read-only to file? 

A) chmod 644 file_name

iii) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode?

A) chmod 740 directory_name

iv) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode and this permissions must be associated to all files and directories/sub-directories underneath this directory?

A) chmod -R 740 directory_name


****************
2) Symbolic Mode 
****************

i) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to file by using absolute mode?

A) chmod u+r+w+x,g+r-w-o,o-r-w-x file_name (or) chmod u+rwx,g+r-w-o,o-rwx file_name (or) chmod u=+rwx,g=+r-w-o,o=-rwx file_name
   

ii) How do I grant the user (owner) read and write, the group read-only, and all others read-only to file? 

A) chmod u+r+w-x,g+r-w-o,o+r-w-x file_name (or) chmod u=+r+w-x,g=+r-w-o,o=+r-w-x file_name

iii) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode?

A) chmod u+r+w+x,g+r-w-o,o-r-w-x directory_name (or) chmod u+rwx,g+r-w-o,o-rwx directory_name (or) chmod u=+rwx,g=+r-w-o,o=-rwx directory_name

iv) How do I grant the user (owner) read, write, and execute, the group read-only, and all others no access to directory by using absolute mode and this permissions must be associated to all files and directories/sub-directories underneath this directory?

A) chmod -R u+r+w+x,g+r-w-o,o-r-w-x directory_name (or) chmod -R u+rwx,g+r-w-o,o-rwx directory_name (or) chmod -R u=+rwx,g=+r-w-o,o=-rwx directory_name

******************
Usage of ugo & rwx
******************

chmod ugo+rwx file_name --> Adding all permissions to file by combinig user,group and others

chmod ug=+r+w+x,o=-rwx file_name --> Restring others except user and group


--------------------------------------------------
Changing owner(user) & group for files/directories
--------------------------------------------------
-----
Files
-----
chown user_name file_name   --> Changing ownership for the file

chown :group_name file_name --> Changing group for the file

chown user_name:group_name file_name --> Changing ownership & group for the file

------
Groups
------
chown user_name directory_name --> Changing ownership for the directory

chown :group_name directory_name --> Changing group for the directory_name

chown user_name:group_name directory --> Changing ownership & group for the directory (Files/Directories permissions under this directory won't effect)

chown -R user_name:group_name directory --> Changing ownership & group for the directory including files and directories underneath it

------------------------------------
Changing File Permissions using Find
------------------------------------

find . -type f -name '*.jpg' -exec chmod 600 {} +                          --> Current Directory

find home/azureuser/folder1/ -type f -name '*.png' -exec chmod 600 {} +    --> Different Directory

sudo find /opt/az -type d -name az -exec chmod 775 {} +  --> Changing permissions for 'az' folder and need sudo